m_szDocSumamry: Why Tesla Motors (TSLA) Stock Hit a One-Year High Today By Andrew Meola | 08/13/14 - 10:15 AM EDT Reprint NEW YORK ( TheStreet ) -- Tesla Motors ( TSLA - Get Report ) rose to a 52-week high of $265.35 on Wednesday after the electric car maker opened two new Supercharger stations in the U.K. Tesla opened one Supercharger station in London at the Hyatt Regency and another at the Hyatt Regency Birmingham, according to engadget.
